    </article>
    <article id="comment_8266465" class="article clearfix reply comment_8266008 staff_comment">

<a href="/tommypenner">
            <img src="http://b.vimeocdn.com/ps/108/108927_30.jpg" alt="Tommy Penner" class="portrait portrait_sm">
    </a>

<div class="comment">
    <p class="meta">
        <a href="/tommypenner" class="meta">Tommy Penner</a> <a tabindex="-1" href="/about" title="Learn more about Vimeo" data-ga-event-click="button|staff_badge_click|staff"><span class="badge_staff">Staff</span></a> <time datetime="2012-11-21T10:39:18-05:00" title="Wednesday, November 21, 2012 10:39 AM" pubdate>2 months ago</time>
            </p>

    
    <div class="text">
                <p class="first">If you see an &quot;LED screen&quot; at a big box store, it actually is an LCD with LED backlighting. As far as I know, LED as a display technology is limited to gigantic public displays -- think of scoreboards at sports stadiums, or Times Square in New York City.</p>    </div>

    </div>

    </article>
