    <div class="text">
                <p class="first">Before I purchased a Panasonic 42&quot; Plasma, I did a ton of research.  LED&#039;s were the new rage at the time with prices dropping and sizes increasing. I went to at least 5 different stores and literally drove hundreds of miles. Montana is a big place. I was in no particular hurry as making certain that the quality was going to be longstanding.  </p>
<p>The final decision came down to the depth of the Blacks and the detail in the shadows. There was really no comparison. Plasma won hand down. I&#039;ve been in the business for 21 years and watched HD come on strong and take over. The next transition will take much longer I suspect because of bandwidth associated with the much larger file sizes of each frame, Compression is your enemy.</p>
<p>So I find it fascinating (and surprisingly logical) that Sony&#039;s archival system includes a return to tape. But that is off the main topic of this thread... Thanks for a nice run down of the current status of  the two formats. It appears little has changed.</p>    </div>

