    <article id="comment_8293189" class="article clearfix main comment_8293189">

<a href="/genekeats">
            <img src="http://b.vimeocdn.com/ps/452/628/4526284_75.jpg" alt="David McRell" class="portrait portrait_lg">
    </a>

<div class="comment">
    <p class="meta">
        <a href="/genekeats" class="meta">David McRell</a>  <time datetime="2012-11-26T02:34:57-05:00" title="Monday, November 26, 2012 2:34 AM" pubdate>2 months ago</time>
            </p>

    
    <div class="text">
                <p class="first">We have been watching movies and TV on an entry-level Panasonic plasma for a few months now. We felt the motion-image qualities are what primarily set these apart from LCD sets. The picture quality is familiar to eyes accustomed to legacy TV and film. The price per screen inch is also attractive.<br>
Negatives: economy settings are too dark, some eyes may be sensitive to color strobing (purple/green fringes as your eyes dart around the screen, notably with B&amp;W content), and you will notice certain image retentions AKA burn-in.</p>    </div>

    </div>

    </article>
    <article id="comment_8308845" class="article clearfix reply comment_8293189 staff_comment">

<a href="/tommypenner">
            <img src="http://b.vimeocdn.com/ps/108/108927_30.jpg" alt="Tommy Penner" class="portrait portrait_sm">
    </a>

<div class="comment">
    <p class="meta">
        <a href="/tommypenner" class="meta">Tommy Penner</a> <a tabindex="-1" href="/about" title="Learn more about Vimeo" data-ga-event-click="button|staff_badge_click|staff"><span class="badge_staff">Staff</span></a> <time datetime="2012-11-28T11:32:54-05:00" title="Wednesday, November 28, 2012 11:32 AM" pubdate>2 months ago</time>
            </p>

    
    <div class="text">
                <p class="first">I&#039;ve never seen or heard of &#039;color strobing&#039; before, I&#039;ll have to look that up!</p>    </div>

    </div>

    </article>
    <article id="comment_8309367" class="article clearfix reply comment_8293189">

<a href="/genekeats">
            <img src="http://b.vimeocdn.com/ps/452/628/4526284_30.jpg" alt="David McRell" class="portrait portrait_sm">
    </a>

<div class="comment">
    <p class="meta">
        <a href="/genekeats" class="meta">David McRell</a>  <time datetime="2012-11-28T12:53:57-05:00" title="Wednesday, November 28, 2012 12:53 PM" pubdate>2 months ago</time>
            </p>

    
    <div class="text">
                <p class="first">&quot;Color strobing&quot; was my description, which is really not be the proper term, but was intended to convey that plasmas (DLP projectors, et al) cycle amongst each color element (RGB) to create the illusion of solid color. These &quot;temporal artifacts&quot; are most noticeable as your eyes scan across white on black text, or high contrast images.</p>    </div>

    </div>

    </article>
    <article id="comment_8310223" class="article clearfix reply comment_8293189 staff_comment">

<a href="/tommypenner">
            <img src="http://b.vimeocdn.com/ps/108/108927_30.jpg" alt="Tommy Penner" class="portrait portrait_sm">
    </a>

